<br>
Mainly I have 2 questions:<br>
<br>
1)  Nice minefield around the coteries =)  Those buried skellies took me by surprise!  They pop if you step on em, but they don't aggro if you are invis.  Of course, when I tried to proximity pull a coterie (who does see invis), invis dropped, and I got two coteries, and a few skellies, and I got stunned, and I died (YEE-HAA!).  Never done much proximity pulling before.  Anyway, my question is, how do you guys pull the vamps?  The skelly/graveyard minefield appeared to be bigger than my casting range, and walking through is suicide (at least on the way out it is ;P)  Is there a certain side you have to pull them from?  Are there certain spells with a big enough range to reach them?  I'm assuming once you get them to come, that they don't bring additional skellies with them.<br>
<br>
BTW, thanks to Filk for the rez =)<br>
<br>
2) Occured to me today.  With that nice big minefield of skellies, are they quaddable?  Man, talk about an endless supply of quad-fodder!!  What are their approx. HPs?  I already saw several people mention that the coteries are poor quad material, but what about the skellies?  And since they are fairly closely spaced, what level do you need to be, without requiring harmony, to single pull them?  And I assume harmony works in ME, but not sure.<br>
<br>
Thanks!<br>
